{"id":16817,"title":"CMS emphasizes quality patient care.","abstract":"The Inpatient Prospective Payment System proposed rule for fiscal 2015 continues the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services' move toward basing reimbursement on quality of care, not quantity. The rule also asks for public input on the two-midnight rule and a policy to address short-stay patients. CMS is implementing the Hospital-Acquired Condition Reduction Program, which penalizes hospitals that perform poorly. The agency proposes to add two safety measures to value-based purchasing in the future.","date":"2014-06-20","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24946382","annotations":[{"name":"Medicare (United States)","weight":0.841827,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medicare_(United_States)"},{"name":"Medicaid","weight":0.810695,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medicaid"},{"name":"Health care","weight":0.797998,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health_care"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.585077,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Hospital","weight":0.496252,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hospital"},{"name":"Policy","weight":0.260168,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Policy"},{"name":"State school","weight":0.23264,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/State_school"},{"name":"Fiscal policy","weight":0.128014,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fiscal_policy"},{"name":"Government agency","weight":0.100392,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_agency"},{"name":"Safety","weight":0.0738637,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Safety"},{"name":"Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services","weight":0.0200356,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Centers_for_Medicare_and_Medicaid_Services"},{"name":"2015","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http: